<FIRST>u i AM-Japan-Markets     01-27 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Japan-Markets,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dollar and Stock Prices Rise Sharply</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Both the dollar and stock prices rose sharply in
Tokyo Friday, buoyed by strong overnight performances in foreign
markets.
   The dollar opened at 128.42 yen and moved between 128.40 and
128.80 yen before closing the week at 128.65 yen, up 1.13 yen from
Thursday's closing.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues gained 134.32 points, or 0.42 percent, to close at a
record high of 31,646.13.
   Exchange dealers said the dollar's rise in Tokyo resulted from
expectations of an improvement in the U.S. gross national product,
scheduled to be released in Washington later Friday.
   The GNP is the total value of goods and services produced by a
nation in a given period of time.
   On the stock market, dealers said the Nikkei's gain was triggered
by the strong 25.18-point rise in the Dow Jones industrial average
in New York on Thursday.
