<HEAD>10 Executed in Zambia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LUSAKA, Zambia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities on Friday hanged 10 men
convicted of crimes ranging from armed robbery to murder, the
government said.
   The hangings at a maximum-security prison in Kabwe, 86 miles
north of Lusaka, were the first executions reported in Zambia for
several years.
   The men were executed before dawn Friday. Five had been sentenced
to death in 1978, but appeals delayed their executions.
   President Kenneth Kaunda has said he opposes the death penalty on
humanitarian grounds. Faced with worsening crime, however,
authorities have taken no action to ban it.
