   Police arrested a suspect Friday in the
shooting of four high school students that a victim said erupted
because of an argument over a chair in the school cafeteria.
   Rodney Reardon, 18, of Washington, was charged with assault with
attempt to murder in the incident that occurred Thursday as shots
were fired into a crowd of students outside Woodrow Wilson High
School in an affluent Washington neighborhood.
   An affadavit presented at Reardon's arraignment in D.C. Superior
