<FIRST>r a AM-Jeremiah-Soviets     01-27 0326</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Jeremiah-Soviets,0337</SECOND>
<HEAD>Pacific Fleet Commander Charges Soviets Breaking Gorbachev Pledge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONOLULU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union has broken Mikhail Gorbachev's
pledge not to increase the number of nuclear weapons in the Pacific,
and there are more spy ships in the Hawaii area, says the commander
of the U.S. Pacific Fleet.
   Adm. David Jeremiah said the Soviets in recent months have added
a new attack submarine to their Pacific fleet, in contradiction to a
speech Gorbachev made last September.
   He quoted the Soviet leader as saying the Soviet Union would not
increase the number of any type of nuclear weapons in the Pacific
region.
   ``Aware of the Asian and Pacific countries' concern, the Soviet
Union will not increase the amount of any nuclear weapons in the
region _ it has already been practicing this for some time _ and is
calling on the United States and other nuclear powers not to deploy
them additionally in the region,'' Gorbachev said in the speech at
Krasnoyarsk, according to the Tass summary.
   The new submarine raised the total of Soviet Delta-class
strategic subs in the Pacific to 17, Jeremiah said in a speech
Thursday during a change-of-command ceremony at Pearl Harbor.
   ``While those of us in senior military positions welcome this new
era of openness with the Kremlin, we remain concerned about the
disparity between what we hear from the Soviets and what we actually
see in the fleet,'' he said.
   He did not say how he knew of the new sub's presence.
   The number of far-ranging deployments by Soviet warships has
decreased since 1985, he said, but the Soviets have increased the
presence of spy ships in Hawaiian waters.
   ``The presence of Soviet intelligence-collection ships in the
near vicinity of the Hawaiian Islands has grown from 60 days in 1986
to more than 250 days in 1987 and 1988,'' Jeremiah said.
   The change-of-command ceremony was for Vice Adm. James Dorsey
Jr., who assumed command of the 3rd Fleet.
</TEXT>
