<FIRST>r a AM-People-McKernan-Snowe     01-27 0208</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-McKernan-Snowe,0216</SECOND>
<HEAD>Maine Governor And Congresswoman To Be Wed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUGUSTA, Maine (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Maine Gov. John R. McKernan and Rep.
Olympia Snowe announced Friday their plans to be married Feb. 24,
according to a statement issued by the governor's office.
   A spokesman for the governor said his staff did not learn of the
news until mid-afternoon. ``I almost fell over, but I wasn't
surprised,'' said press secretary Willis Lyford.
   Lyford said the couple plan to have a church wedding in Lewiston,
but that none of the details have been firmed up.
   Neither McKernan nor Snowe could be reached immediately; both
were out of their offices during the afternoon.
   McKernan and Snowe, both Republicans, served together in the U.S.
House of Representatives from 1983 to 1986 and in the Maine House of
Representatives during the 1970s, and have dated for several years.
They plan to continue separate political careers, the governor's
office said.
   McKernan, 40, took office as chief executive in January 1987,
becoming Maine's first Republican governor in two decades, after two
terms in Congress.
   McKernan is divorced and the father of a teen-age son.
   Snowe, 41, entered the U.S. House in 1979 and was elected last
year to her sixth term. She was widowed in 1973.
</TEXT>
