<FIRST>r f BC-Tandy-Buyback     01-27 0142</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Tandy-Buyback,0150</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tandy To Repurchase Up To 10 Million Common Shares</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tandy Corp. announced Friday that it
planned to buy back up to 10 million of its outstanding common
shares, a move that could cost the electronics company more than
$400 million.
   ``Basically, this affirms our belief that Tandy stock has been
undervalued,'' said Phillip M. Bradtmiller, a Tandy spokesman.
``This is an efficient use of our excess resources.''
   The company said it planned to buy the stock from time to time in
the open market and finance the purchases through current funds and
short-term borrowings.
   Tandy was trading at $41.87{ a share in late-afternoon dealings
Friday on the New York Stock Exchange, giving the buyback plan a
value of around $418.75 million.
   At the end of 1988 Tandy had about 90 million common shares
outstanding.
