   Gold for delivery in February settled at $396.10 a troy ounce
compared with $409.30 a week earlier; while silver for delivery in
March fell to $5.935 a troy ounce from $6.245 a week earlier.
   Crude oil prices rallied while heating oil and unleaded gas
declined at the New York Mercantile Exchange.
   March crude oil settled at $17.74 a barrel, compared to $17.33 a
week earlier; February heating oil fell to 51.98 cents a gallon from
52.60 cents; and February unleaded gas dipped to 49.59 cents a
gallon from 51.78 cents a week earlier.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End adv weekend editions Jan. 28-29.</NOTE>
