<FIRST>u f AM-Smartfoods-Frito-Lay     01-27 0282</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Smartfoods-Frito-Lay,0293</SECOND>
<HEAD>Smartfoods Sells Out To Frito-Lay</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN DIAMOND</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Smartfoods Inc., a maker of cheddar cheese popcorn
that once boasted of its tiny size and developed an avid following
in New England, agreed to sell out to snack-food giant Frito-Lay
Inc. for $14.5 million, officials said Friday.
   Smartfoods shareholders voted overwhelmingly Thursday to sell
their shares in the privately held company, said Thomas Protheroe, a
Smartfoods distributor who provided the selling price. Neither
company would disclose the value of the deal.
   Smartfoods, which touts its ``all natural'' product in shiny
black-and-gold bags, will continue to operate unchanged, Frito-Lay
said.
   While Frito-Lay and Smartfoods officials said the deal would
bring a largely Northeastern product to a nationwide market,
distributors such as Protheroe were angry because Frito-Lay would be
taking over their lucrative distribution of the popcorn.
   ``We're finished,'' said Protheroe.
   Frito-Lay spokeswoman Beverly Holmes said in a telephone
interview that the buyout evolved from the desire of Smartfoods
officials to expand their distribution.
   ``We thought it was a very logical fit,'' Holmes said. ``We do
have a national distribution system. And obviously they have an
excellent product and a good marketing organization. We don't plan
to make any changes with the company.''
   Dallas-based Frito-Lay, a subsidiary of Pepsico Inc., had sales
of $3.7 billion last year. Smartfoods, based in the Boston suburb of
Marlboro, had sales of about $12 million in the past 12 months, said
spokeswoman Celia Gorlich.
   Smartfoods originally billed itself as the ``little guy.''
Smartfoods bags still carry the message: ``Instead of spending
millions on advertising like the junk food companies, we spend most
of our money on the highest quality ingredients.''
</TEXT>
