<HEAD>Newhouse Denies Rumors Newspaper for Sale</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES circulation figures in last graf; Also moved on general
newswires</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rumors that The Oregonian is for sale are
unfounded, the president of the newspaper's parent company said
Friday.
   ``The rumor has it that Times Mirror has bought The Oregonian or
that other groups have bought The Oregonian. It is totally untrue,''
Donald Newhouse, president of Advance Publications, said in a
telephone interview from Washington.
   Times Mirror publishes the Los Angeles Times and other daily
newspapers.
   Two local radio stations reported the rumor Thursday, along with
a denial issued by The Oregonian.
   Newhouse said there are no plans to sell the newspaper, ``not
even a thought about it.''
   ``I do not know where the rumor originated,'' he said. ``It just
has blossomed forth.''
   The Oregonian, Portland's only daily newspaper, has a daily
circulation of 317,711 and a Sunday circulation of 409,562.
</TEXT>
