<FILEID>AP-NR-01-27-89 2032EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Media     01-27 0202</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Media,0210</SECOND>
<HEAD>Media General Earnings Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RICHMOND, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Media General Inc. reported a fourth-quarter
loss Friday and said 1988 earnings fell 79.4 percent, largely
because of costs associated with the sale of its broadcast services
business.
   The diversified communications company lost $29.6 million on
revenue of $191.4 million for the last three months of 1988, vs. a
profit of $11.4 million or 40 cents a share on revenue of $183.8
million a year earlier.
   For all of 1988, Media General said earnings totaled $8.81
million or 31 cents a share, down fro $42.9 million or $1.50 a share
in 1987. The drop came despite a 5.6 percent increase in revenues to
$755.7 million, up from $715.3 million in 1987.
   Most of the decline was attributed by the company to the sale of
its Broadcast Service operation to members of the unit's management,
resulting in a pretax charge of $54.9 million.
   James E. Evans, president and chief executive officer, said each
of the company's three major operations _ newspapers, broadcast and
newsprint _ participated in the revenue increase.
   ``In all, 1988 was a year in which Media General made important
progress in redefining the company's hard core businesses,'' Evans
said.
</TEXT>
